“Despite the pandemic, I left energetic...”
> Is this supposed to be “felt energetic”?
Really, the pandemic has not been an issue with work or relationship. While the work/life boundary is blurred it is still a blessing to be working from home as I’m able to interact with my wife throughout the day and such m not as stressed as a result, and no wasted time commuting 3hrs a day.
My biggest pandemic stressor is being away from my kids. I had to move several years ago due to a lack of local job opportunities and unemployment. I balanced that with visits every 3 weeks. Since pandemic I haven’t been able to visit since Feb - zoom calls work great for work but are so inadequate for spending time with your kids. I miss them horribly. That is my life and relationship stress
